HOST: http://api.unityprofiles.com/

--- Unity-Profiles ---

---
A web application for setting up profiles that define the behavior of your Unity3D games. It aims to provide an easy interface to allow developers to enable designers and managers to do all the tweaking and to be able to share different settings between them.
The Github repository is hosted at [https://github.com/NoxHarmonium/unity-profiles](https://github.com/NoxHarmonium/unity-profiles)
---

--
Administration
The following is a section of resources related to managing user authentication etc.
--

Authenicate user and start session.
Automatically logs out current user if applicable.
POST /login
> Accept: application/json
{ "username": "user@domain.com", "password": "password" }
< 200
+++++
< 401
< Content-Type: application/json
{ detail: "Incorrect username/password" }



Create a new user
PUT /users/{username}
> Accept: application/json
{ "username": "user@domain.com", "password": "password" }
< 201 
+++++
< 409 
< Content-Type: application/json
{ detail: "User already exists" }


Get information on a specific user
GET /users/{username}
< 200
< Content-Type: application/json
{
   "email" : "test@test.com"
}
+++++
< 404 
{ detail: "User doesn't exist" }

Change a user's password
The user must be logged out
POST /users/{username}/password/
> Accept: application/json
{ "oldPassword" : "password", "newPassword": "newpassword" }
< 200
+++++
< 401
< Content-Type: application/json
{ "detail": "Incorrect password"  }
+++++
< 400
< Content-Type: application/json
{ "detail": "Cannot change password when logged in" }

Reset a user's password
Emails the user with a temporary password that they can use to change their password that is valid for 10 minutes
POST /usets/{username}/resetpassword/
< 200
+++++
< 500
{ "detail": "There was a problem sending the email" }

Logout the currently authenticated user
GET /logout
< 200



