Project Manipulation
The following is a section of resources related to creating/manipulating the projects that the profiles apply to
--


Gets a list of projects that you are authorised to see. Will only return the latest version
GET /projects
< 200
< Content-Type: application/json
{
    projects : [
        {
        "name": "Test project",
        "owner": "user@domain.com",
        "description": "A test project for unity-profiles",
        "version" : "1"
        }
    ]
}

Gets information on a the lastest version of a specific project by name
GET /projects/{proj_name}
< 200
< Content-Type: application/json
{
    "name": "Test project",
    "owner": "user@domain.com",
    "description": "A test project for unity-profiles",
    "version" : "1"
}

Gets information on a specific version of a specific project by name
GET /projects/{proj_name}/{proj_version}
< 200
< Content-Type: application/json
{
    "name": "Test project",
    "owner": "user@domain.com",
    "description": "A test project for unity-profiles",
    "version" : "1"
}

Creates a new  project by name and version
PUT /projects/{proj_name}/{proj_version}
> Accept: application/json
> Content-Type: application/json
{
    "name": "Test project",
    "owner": "user@domain.com",
    "description": "A test project for unity-profiles",
    "version" : "1"
}
< 201 


